M||tx|---
M|Over|tx|**Writing skills IS tst-Driven dv applied to process doc.**
M|Over|tx|**Personal skills live in ag-specific directories (`~/.claude/skills` for Claude Code, `~/.ag/skills/` for Codex)**
M|Over|tx|You write tst cases (pressure scenarios w/ subagents), watch them fail (baseline behavior), write the skill (doc), watch tests pass (ag comply), and rf (close loopholes).
M|Over|**Co|** If you didn't watch an ag fail w/o the skill, you don't know if the skill teaches the right thing.
M|Over|**RE|** You MUST understand superpowers:tst-driven-dv before using this skill. That skill defines the fundamental RED-GREEN-rf cycle. This skill adapts TDD to doc.
M|Over|**Of|** For Anthropic's official skill authoring best practices, see anthropic-best-practices.md. This document provides additional patterns and guidelines that complement the TDD-focused approach in this skill.
M|What|tx|A **skill** is a reference guide for proven techniques, patterns, or tools. Skills help future Claude instances find and apply effective approaches.
M|What|**Sk|** Reusable techniques, patterns, tools, reference guides
M|What|**Sk|** Narratives abt how you solved a problem once
M|TDD |tx|\| TDD Concept \| Skill Creation \|
M|TDD |tx|\|-------------\|----------------\|
M|TDD |tx|\| **tst case** \| Pressure scenario w/ subagent \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Production code** \| Skill document (SKILL.md) \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **tst fails (RED)** \| ag violates rule w/o skill (baseline) \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **tst passes (GREEN)** \| ag complies w/ skill present \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **rf** \| Close loopholes while maintaining compliance \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Write tst first** \| Run baseline scenario BEFORE writing skill \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Watch it fail** \| Document exact rationalizations ag uses \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Minimal code** \| Write skill addressing those specific violations \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **Watch it pass** \| Verify ag now complies \|
M|TDD |tx|\| **rf cycle** \| Find new rationalizations → plug → re-verify \|
M|TDD |tx|The entire skill creation process follows RED-GREEN-rf.
M|When|**Cr|**
M|When|it|Technique wasn't intuitively obvious to you
M|When|it|You'd reference this again across projects
M|When|it|Pattern applies broadly (not project-specific)
M|When|it|Others wld benefit
M|When|**Do|**
M|When|it|One-off solutions
M|When|it|Standard practices well-documented elsewhere
M|When|it|Project-specific conventions (put in CLAUDE.md)
M|When|it|Mechanical constraints (if it's enforceable w/ regex/validation, automate it—save doc for judgment calls)
M|Tech|tx|Concrete method w/ steps to follow (condition-based-waiting, root-cause-tracing)
M|Patt|tx|Way of thinking abt problems (flatten-w/-flags, tst-invariants)
M|Refe|tx|ap doc, syntax guides, tool doc (office doc)
