M|Dire|tx|2. **Reusable tools** - Scripts, utilities, templates
M|Dire|**Ke|**
M|Dire|it|Principles and concepts
M|Dire|it|Code patterns (< 50 lines)
M|Dire|it|Everything else
M|SKIL|**Fr|**
M|SKIL|- Tw|`name` and `description` (see [agentskills.io/specification](https://agentskills.io/specification) for all supported fields)
M|SKIL|it|Max 1024 characters total
M|SKIL|- `n|Use letters, numbers, and hyphens only (no parentheses, special chars)
M|SKIL|- `d|Third-person, describes ONLY when to use (NOT what it does)
M|SKIL|it|Start w/ "Use when..." to focus on triggering conditions
M|SKIL|it|Include specific symptoms, situations, and contexts
M|SKIL|it|**NEVER summarize the skill's process or workflow** (see CSO section for why)
M|SKIL|it|Keep under 500 characters if possible
M|SKIL|tx|```markdown
M|SKIL|tx|---
M|SKIL|name|Skill-Name-w/-Hyphens
M|SKIL|desc|Use when [specific triggering conditions and symptoms]
M|SKIL|tx|---
M|Over|tx|What is this? Core principle in 1-2 sentences.
M|When|tx|[Small inline flowchart IF decision non-obvious]
M|When|tx|Bullet list w/ SYMPTOMS and use cases
M|When|tx|When NOT to use
M|Core|tx|Before/after code comparison
M|Quic|tx|Table or bullets for scanning common operations
M|Impl|tx|Inline code for simple patterns
M|Impl|tx|Link to file for heavy reference or reusable tools
M|Comm|tx|What goes wrong + fixes
M|Real|tx|Concrete results
M|Real|tx|```
M|Clau|**Cr|** Future Claude needs to FIND your skill
M|1. R|**Pu|** Claude reads description to decide which skills to load for a given task. Make it answer: "shd I read this skill right now?"
M|1. R|**Fo|** Start w/ "Use when..." to focus on triggering conditions
M|1. R|ct|Description = When to Use, NOT What the Skill Does**
M|1. R|tx|The description shd ONLY describe triggering conditions. Do NOT summarize the skill's process or workflow in the description.
M|1. R|**Wh|** Testing revealed that when a description summarizes the skill's workflow, Claude may follow the description instead of reading the full skill cn. A description saying "code rv btw tasks" caused Claude to do ONE rv, even though the skill's flowchart clearly showed TWO reviews (spec compliance then code qual).
M|1. R|tx|When the description was changed to just "Use when executing implementation plans w/ independent tasks" (no workflow summary), Claude correctly read the flowchart and followed the two-stage rv process.
M|1. R|**Th|** Descriptions that summarize workflow cr a shortcut Claude will take. The skill body becomes doc Claude skips.
M|1. R|tx|```yaml
M|❌ BA|desc|Use when executing plans - dispatches subagent per task w/ code rv btw tasks
M|❌ BA|desc|Use for TDD - write tst first, watch it fail, write minimal code, rf
M|✅ GO|desc|Use when executing implementation plans w/ independent tasks in the current sn
M|✅ GO|desc|Use when implementing any feature or bugfix, before writing implementation code
M|✅ GO|tx|```
M|✅ GO|cn|**
M|✅ GO|it|Use concrete triggers, symptoms, and situations that signal this skill applies
M|✅ GO|it|Describe the *problem* (race conditions, inconsistent behavior) not *language-specific symptoms* (setTimeout, sleep)
M|✅ GO|it|Keep triggers technology-agnostic unless the skill itself is technology-specific
M|✅ GO|it|If skill is technology-specific, make that explicit in the trigger
M|✅ GO|it|Write in third person (injected into sy pm)
M|✅ GO|it|**NEVER summarize the skill's process or workflow**
