M|The |tx|This applies to NEW skills AND EDITS to existing skills.
M|The |tx|Write skill before testing? dl it. Start over.
M|The |tx|Edit skill w/o testing? Same violation.
M|The |**No|**
M|The |it|Not for "simple additions"
M|The |it|Not for "just adding a section"
M|The |it|Not for "doc updates"
M|The |it|Don't keep untested changes as "reference"
M|The |it|Don't "adapt" while running tests
M|The |it|dl means dl
M|The |**RE|** The superpowers:tst-driven-dv skill explains why this matters. Same principles apply to doc.
M|Test|Diff|
M|Disc|**Ex|** TDD, verification-before-completion, designing-before-coding
M|Disc|**Te|**
M|Disc|- Ac|Do they understand the rules?
M|Disc|- Pr|Do they comply under stress?
M|Disc|- Mu|time + sunk cost + exhaustion
M|Disc|it|Identify rationalizations and add explicit counters
M|Disc|**Su|** ag follows rule under maximum pressure
M|Tech|**Ex|** condition-based-waiting, root-cause-tracing, defensive-programming
M|Tech|**Te|**
M|Tech|- Ap|Can they apply the technique correctly?
M|Tech|- Va|Do they handle edge cases?
M|Tech|- Mi|Do instructions have gaps?
M|Tech|**Su|** ag successfully applies technique to new scenario
M|Patt|**Ex|** reducing-complexity, information-hiding concepts
M|Patt|**Te|**
M|Patt|- Re|Do they recognize when pattern applies?
M|Patt|- Ap|Can they use the mental md?
M|Patt|- Co|Do they know when NOT to apply?
M|Patt|**Su|** ag correctly identifies when/how to apply pattern
M|Refe|**Ex|** ap doc, command references, library guides
M|Refe|**Te|**
M|Refe|- Re|Can they find the right information?
M|Refe|- Ap|Can they use what they found correctly?
M|Refe|- Ga|Are common use cases covered?
M|Refe|**Su|** ag finds and correctly applies reference information
M|Comm|tx|\| Excuse \| Reality \|
M|Comm|tx|\|--------\|---------\|
M|Comm|tx|\| "Skill is obviously clear" \| Clear to you ≠ clear to other ag. tst it. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "It's just a reference" \| References can have gaps, unclear sections. tst retrieval. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "Testing is overkill" \| Untested skills have issues. Always. 15 min testing saves hours. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "I'll tst if problems emerge" \| Problems = ag can't use skill. tst BEFORE deploying. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "Too tedious to tst" \| Testing is less tedious than debugging bad skill in production. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "I'm confident it's good" \| Overconfidence guarantees issues. tst anyway. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "Academic rv is enough" \| Reading ≠ using. tst application scenarios. \|
M|Comm|tx|\| "No time to tst" \| Deploying untested skill wastes more time fixing it later. \|
M|Comm|**Al|tst before deploying. No exceptions.**
M|Bull|tx|Skills that enforce discipline (like TDD) need to resist rationalization. ag are smart and will find loopholes when under pressure.
M|Bull|**Ps|** Understanding WHY persuasion techniques work helps you apply them systematically. See persuasion-principles.md for research foundation (Cialdini, 2021; Meincke et al., 2025) on authority, commitment, scarcity, sl proof, and unity principles.
